2Y
f_{X+2Y} (a)
 \begin{align*} f_{X+2Y}(a) &= \frac{d}{da} \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} F_X(a-2y) f_Y(y) ~ dy  \\ &= \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} \frac{d}{da} F_X(a-2y) f_Y(y) ~ dy \\ &= \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} f_X(a-2y) f_Y(y) ~ dy \end{align*} 
[0,1]
 f_X(a) = f_Y(a) = \begin{cases} 1, & 0 \lt a \lt 1, \\ 0, &\text{otherwise}. \end{cases} 
 f_{X + 2Y}(a) = \int_{-\infty}^{+\infty} f_X(a-2y) f_Y(y) ~ dy \quad \text{for } 0 \lt a \lt 1. 
 f_{X + 2Y}(a-2) = \int_0^a dy = a. 
